---
// Standalone live demo of the canvas-2D renderer binding.
//
// This is a plain Astro page (outside the Starlight docs content collection) so the
// llms-txt generator — which serializes docs pages to text and cannot render an
// interactive React island — never touches it. Docs pages LINK here.
import Canvas2dBoardIsland from '../../components/Canvas2dBoardIsland.tsx';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
		<title>Live demo — canvas-2D binding · declarative-hex-worlds</title>
		<style>
			:root { color-scheme: light dark; }
			body {
				margin: 0;
				font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
				background: #14171a;
				color: #e8e6df;
				display: flex;
				justify-content: center;
			}
			main { max-width: 900px; padding: 2rem 1.25rem; width: 100%; }
			a { color: #a7c957; }
			h1 { font-size: 1.5rem; }
			.frame { margin: 1.5rem 0; }
			p { line-height: 1.6; }
			code { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08); padding: 0.1em 0.35em; border-radius: 4px; }
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<main>
			<p><a href={base}>← declarative-hex-worlds docs</a></p>
			<h1>Live demo — the canvas-2D binding</h1>
			<p>
				The board below is <strong>not a screenshot</strong>. It is the reference example
				game — the same deterministic world used throughout the docs — compiled from a JSON
				scenario into a live Koota runtime and rendered in your browser through the
				<code>declarative-hex-worlds/canvas2d</code> binding.
			</p>
			<div class="frame">
				<Canvas2dBoardIsland client:only="react" />
			</div>
			<p>
				The signals-and-bindings architecture means one world drives any renderer. The core
				is renderer-free — it emits reactive Koota-trait signals; a binding subscribes and
				reconciles its own scene. <code>/canvas2d</code> turns each 2D placement into a
				sprite blit (zero renderer dependency); <code>/three</code> takes the same signals
				and reconciles a Three.js scene for 3D GLTF models. The sprite sheet here is
				generated procedurally so the demo needs no downloaded art.
			</p>
		</main>
	</body>
</html>
